race.comment: JUST ALBERT (3) has been winning by big spaces and the step up to the mile shouldn't bother. Keeps the handy 3kg claim and can go on with the job. ROCK REVOLUTION (1) switched from a top Sydney yard and looked a run short. His Victorian provincial form reads well for this contest and the claim is handy Quick improvement is on the cards. ITWASONLYAKISS (2) is a former Victorian who will show more over a mile. He won a 58 at Donald before the spell. The gate is awkward but he'll be around the mark with a decent ride. BEATIFICATION (7) draws low and presents today on the fresh side. He would be in the finish if he put his best foot forward.
